{"title":"Fizik Vega Carbon: Infinito and beyond","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/sponsored/fizik-vega-carbon","date":1749114116000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/sponsored/fizik-vega-carbon\">Fizik Vega Carbon: Infinito and beyond</a></p>\n\n<p>Over the past few years, Fizik’s Infinito models have proved incredibly popular among both amateurs and pros, with Geraint Thomas using a pair during his 2018 Tour de France victory. The Vega Carbon replaces the Infinito design and quite literally has big shoes to fill, but Nicola Poletti, Fizik’s global business manager, is confident.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘The Vega Carbon not only replaces the Infinito but exceeds the design in every aspect,’ says Poletti. ‘The increased performance starts with our new shape.’</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-647x970.webp\" alt=\"Fizik Vega Carbon\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-647x970.webp 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-200x300.webp 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-768x1151.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-1025x1536.webp 1025w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-750x1124.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2-1140x1709.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-2.webp 1200w\" /><figcaption>Tapestry / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Vega’s shape has been revised from Fizik’s previous high-end models to widen the toe box to both broaden appeal and enhance comfort.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘We’ve also improved arch support and reduced the heel-to-toe drop for a more neutral foot position, plus straightened the shoe relative to the cleat position to promote better ankle, knee and hip alignment,’ says Poletti.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-647x970.webp\" alt=\"Fizik Vega Carbon\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-647x970.webp 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-200x300.webp 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-768x1151.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-1025x1536.webp 1025w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-750x1124.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3-1140x1709.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/06/fizik-vega-carbon-3.webp 1200w\" /><figcaption>Fizik’s shoes are often known for being narrow, but the Vega features a wider toe box for broader appeal and improved comfort.</figcaption><figcaption>Tapestry / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The improved ergonomics are supported by the use of Fizik’s Aeroweave mesh upper, a net-like structure with different weave patterns in particular areas of the shoe to provide malleability and security in the places they are needed most, while naturally offering plenty of ventilation. The upper wraps the foot and encloses the carbon sole plate.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘Integrating the sole into the shoe structure in this way, rather than planting it onto the bottom, improves stability and reduces stack height for better power transfer into the pedals,’ says Poletti.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It sounds like the Vega Carbon has what it takes to continue the Infinito’s impressive legacy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• <strong>Fizik Vega Carbon, £389.99, <a href=\"https://www.fizik.com/uk_en/vega.html\" target=\"_blank\">fizik.com</a></strong></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-vega-carbon-shoes\">Fizik’s new top-of-the-range Vega Carbon shoes use a wider last for added comfort</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fizik-helmets\">Fizik releases its first helmets, including two road, one TT and one MTB</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/fizik-saddles-insider\">Best seat in the house: behind the scenes at Fizik</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                         